						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Optimising-the-use-of-water-for-drip-irrigation-in-Burkina-Faso" title="Optimising the use of water for drip irrigation in Burkina Faso" alt="link">Optimising the use of water for drip irrigation in Burkina Faso</a></h2>

	
					<p>This article describes the application of wireless sensor technology, adapted to local climatic conditions, to alert small producers in the semi-arid regions of Burkina Faso on the best time to irrigate, according to the plants’ needs, resulting in higher yields and water saving. This new technology is based on low-cost wireless weather stations that automatically broadcast reliable data. Hydrometeorological measures are made available to local users in real time through the mobile telephone network and the <a href="http://www.climaps.com" target="_blank">Climaps websit</a>e. The technology was developed in a R&amp;D project of the Cooperation &amp; Development Centre (CODEV) of the <a href="http://cooperation.epfl.ch/HomePage" target="_blank">École polytechnique fédérale de Lausanne (EPFL)</a>, Switzerland, in partnership with the start-up <a href="http://www.sensorscope.ch/" target="_blank">Sensorscope</a>. (EPFL, 15/12/2014)</p>
							<p><span class="date">5/02/2015</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Optimising-the-use-of-water-for-drip-irrigation-in-Burkina-Faso">Read more...</a>
</div>
